data.enText: commoner
commonest

data.text: More common and most common are more frequent.

data.chText: 常见的；通常的；普遍的
data.enText: happening often; existing in large numbers or in many places

data.chText: 杰克逊是常见的英语人名。
data.enText: Jackson is a common English name.

data.chText: 乳腺癌是这个国家妇女中最常见的一种癌症。
data.enText: Breast cancer is the most common form of cancer among women in this country.

data.chText: 有些曾经随处可见的鸟类现在日益稀少。
data.enText: Some birds which were once a common sight are now becoming rare.

data.chText: 常犯的拼写错误
data.enText: a common spelling mistake

data.chText: 共有的；共享的；共同的
data.enText: shared by or belonging to two or more people or by the people in a group

data.chText: 他们在摄影方面兴趣相投。
data.enText: They share a common interest in photography.

data.chText: 所有人类语言共有的基本特征
data.enText: basic features which are common to all human languages

data.chText: 我们在为一个共同的目标一起工作。
data.enText: We are working together for a common purpose.

data.chText: 土地的共同所有权
data.enText: common ownership of the land

data.chText: 作出这个决定是为了共同的利益。
data.enText: This decision was taken for the common good (= the advantage of everyone) .

data.chText: 这是苏格兰公认的最美丽的海岸。
data.enText: It is, by common consent , Scotland's prettiest coast (= everyone agrees that it is) .

data.chText: 普通的；平常的；寻常的；平凡的
data.enText: ordinary; not unusual or special

data.chText: 园地里常见的青蛙
data.enText: the common garden frog

data.chText: 莎士比亚的作品在他那个年代很受平民百姓的欢迎。
data.enText: Shakespeare's work was popular among the common people in his day.

data.chText: 在多数人的眼里她只不过是个普通的罪犯。
data.enText: In most people's eyes she was nothing more than a common criminal .

data.chText: 你还以为他会懂得起码的礼貌去道个歉呢。
data.enText: You'd think he'd have the common courtesy to apologize (= this would be the polite behaviour that people would expect) .

data.chText: 出于礼貌，该让她知道正在发生的事。
data.enText: It's only common decency to let her know what's happening (= people would expect it) .

data.chText: 粗俗的；庸俗的
data.enText: typical of sb from a low social class and not having good manners

data.chText: 她认为他很粗俗且无教养。
data.enText: She thought he was very common and uneducated.
common or garden
garden-variety

data.chText: 普通的；平常的；一般的
data.enText: ordinary; with no special features
the common touch

data.chText: （有权势者或名人的）平易近人的品质
data.enText: the ability of a powerful or famous person to talk to and understand ordinary people
make common cause with sb

data.chText: 与某人联合起来，与某人合作（以达到共同的目的）
data.enText: to be united with sb about sth that you both agree on, believe in or wish to achieve
be common/public knowledge

data.chText: 常识；众所周知
data.enText: to be sth that everyone knows, especially in a particular community or group

data.chText: 公共用地；公地
data.enText: an area of open land in a town or village that anyone may use

data.chText: 我们在公地上散步。
data.enText: We went for a walk on the common.

data.chText: 温布尔登公地
data.enText: Wimbledon Common

data.chText: （学校、大学等的）学生公共食堂
data.enText: a large room where students can eat in a school, college, etc.

data.chText: 学生公共食堂在体育馆的旁边。
data.enText: The commons is next to the gym.
have sth in common (with sb)

data.chText: （想法、兴趣等方面）相同
data.enText: to have the same interests, ideas, etc. as sb else

data.chText: 我和蒂姆毫无共同之处。
data.enText: Tim and I have nothing in common./I have nothing in common with Tim.
have sth in common (with sth)

data.chText: 有相同的特征（或特点等）
data.enText: to have the same features, characteristics, etc.

data.chText: 这两种文化具有许多相同之处。
data.enText: The two cultures have a lot in common.
in common

data.chText: 共有；公有
data.enText: by everyone in a group

data.chText: 作为共同租赁人，他们共同占用这份房地产。
data.enText: They hold the property as tenants in common.
in common with sb/sth

data.chText: 与…相同
data.enText: in the same way as sb/sth

data.chText: 与许多其他工业化国家一样，英国在过去100年里经历了重大的变化。
data.enText: Britain, in common with many other industrialized countries, has experienced major changes over the last 100 years.

means: (学校、大学等的)学生公共食堂

ex.chText: 一种普遍的错误观念认为：东西越贵，质量就会越好。
ex.enText: It is a popular misunderstanding that the higher the price is, the better the product will be.

ex.chText: 对于实名购买火车票制度，民众意见有分歧吗？
ex.enText: Was popular opinion divided on the real-name train ticket system?

synonyms.bx: 指想法、信仰等为大部分人所持有并接受的，只作定语。

ex.chText: 成年人失眠是常有的事。
ex.enText: Insomnia is fairly common among adults.

ex.chText: 小孩子不敢一个人睡觉是很常见的。
ex.enText: It is common for children to be afraid of sleeping alone.

synonyms.bx: 指经常在多人身上或多个地方发生的。

ex.chText: 这部电影是关于普通人的。
ex.enText: This movie is about ordinary people.

ex.chText: 体育锻炼理应是日常生活的一部分。
ex.enText: Physical exercise should be part of ordinary life.

ex.chText: 我推荐这本小说是因为它是用平凡的语言写成的。
ex.enText: I recommend this novel because it is written in ordinary language.

synonyms.bx: 指平常的，没有不同或特别之处的。

ex.chText: 房价是人们普遍关注的一个问题。
ex.enText: House price is a topic of universal interest.

synonyms.bx: 指包括某一群体中的每个人在内的，无一例外。

synonym.guide: 导航词义：普通的，普遍的

tr: a piece of open land for recreational use in an urban area
example: they went for a walk in the park

tr: having no special distinction or quality
example: it is common knowledge that she lives alone

tr: belonging to or participated in by a community as a whole
example: common lands are set aside for use by all members of a community

tr: being or characteristic of or appropriate to everyday language
example: the vulgar tongue of the masses
the technical and vulgar names for an animal species

tr: of or associated with the great masses of people
example: the common people in those days suffered greatly
behavior that branded him as common

tr: lacking refinement or cultivation or taste
example: he had coarse manners but a first-rate mind
behavior that branded him as common
an untutored and uncouth human being
an uncouth soldier--a real tough guy
appealing to the vulgar taste for violence
the vulgar display of the newly rich

tr: common to or shared by two or more parties
example: the mutual interests of management and labor

tr: of low or inferior quality or value
example: of what coarse metal ye are molded"- Shakespear
produced...the common cloths used by the poorer population

value.def: If something is common, it is found in large numbers or it happens often.

example.ex: His name was Hansen, a common name in Norway...
example.tran: 他的名字叫汉森，在挪威是一个常见的名字。

example.ex: Oil pollution is the commonest cause of death for seabirds...
example.tran: 石油污染是造成海鸟死亡最常见的原因。

example.ex: Earthquakes are not common in this part of the world...
example.tran: 地震在这一带不常发生。

example.ex: It was common practice for prisoners to carve objects from animal bones to pass the time.
example.tran: 用动物骨头雕刻物品是犯人打发时间的一种常见做法。

example.ex: Parsley is probably the most commonly used of all herbs.
example.tran: 欧芹可能是用得最多的一种药草。

value.def: If something is common to two or more people or groups, it is done, possessed, or used by them all.

example.ex: Moldavians and Romanians share a common language...
example.tran: 摩尔达维亚人和罗马尼亚人使用同一种语言。

example.ex: Such behaviour is common to all young people.
example.tran: 这种行为在年轻人中司空见惯。

value.def: When there are more animals or plants of a particular species than there are of related species, then the first species is called common .

example.ex: ...the common house fly.
example.tran: 常见的家蝇

value.def: Common is used to indicate that someone or something is of the ordinary kind and not special in any way.

example.ex: Democracy might elevate the common man to a position of political superiority...
example.tran: 民主也许能提升普通人的政治地位，让他们产生优越感。

example.ex: Common salt is made up of 40% sodium and 60% chloride.
example.tran: 食盐由40%的钠和60%的氯化物构成。

value.def: Common decency or common courtesy is the decency or courtesy which most people have. You usually talk about this when someone has not shown these characteristics in their behaviour to show your disapproval of them.

example.ex: It is common decency to give your seat to anyone in greater need...
example.tran: 给更有需要的人让座是最起码的礼貌。

example.ex: He didn't have the common courtesy to ask permission.
example.tran: 他连邀准这种最起码的礼貌都没有。

value.def: You can use common to describe knowledge, an opinion, or a feeling that is shared by people in general.

example.ex: It is common knowledge that swimming is one of the best forms of exercise.
example.tran: 大家都知道游泳是最好的锻炼方式之一。

example.ex: ...the common view that acupuncture is only a fringe area of medicine.
example.tran: 针灸仅仅是医学的一个边缘领域的这种普遍看法

value.tran: (知识等)众所周知的，共有的，共识的

example.ex: A little adolescent rebellion is commonly believed to be healthy.
example.tran: 大家一致认为，青少年有点叛逆是正常的。

value.def: If you describe someone or their behaviour as common, you mean that they show a lack of taste, education, and good manners.

example.ex: She might be a little common at times, but she was certainly not boring.
example.tran: 她有时候可能有点粗俗，但绝对不会让人生厌。

value.def: A common is an area of grassy land, usually in or near a village or small town, where the public is allowed to go.

example.ex: We are warning women not to go out on to the common alone.
example.tran: 我们告诫女性不要独自去公共草地。

example.ex: ...Wimbledon Common.
example.tran: 温布尔登公地

posc.def: In American English, the commons is also used.

example.ex: ...people who have the greatest need for the use of the commons, the public space.
example.tran: 对公共草地这种公用空间需求最大的人

value.tran: (通常指村庄、小镇或其附近的)公共草地

value.def: The Commons is the same as the House of Commons. The members of the House of Commons can also be referred to as the Commons .

example.ex: The Prime Minister is to make a statement in the Commons this afternoon...
example.tran: 今天下午首相将在下议院发表声明。

example.ex: The Commons has spent over three months on the bill.
example.tran: 下议院在这项议案上已经花了3个多月的时间。

value.tran: 同 the House of Commons;(亦指)下议员议员们

value.def: If two or more things have something in common, they have the same characteristic or feature.

example.ex: The oboe and the clarinet have got certain features in common...
example.tran: 双簧管和单簧管有些相似之处。

example.ex: In common with most Italian lakes, access to the shores of Orta is restricted.
example.tran: 和大部分意大利湖泊一样，奥尔塔湖岸不对公众开放。

value.def: If two or more people have something in common, they share the same interests or experiences.

example.ex: He had very little in common with his sister.
example.tran: 他和姐姐几乎没有什么共同语言。
